verge of tears I felt a profound regret a regret forI knew not what Was it for the beating of the temple drums or the shouting of the populace as the king was raised on high Was it for the human sacrifices of olden times It was for none of these individually but for something at the back of them all some living spirit and divine courage that existed in ancient times of which Taputapuatea was a mute symbol It was something that we Polynesians have lost and cannot find something that we yearn for
